title: Three Millburn High School teams hosting county tourney matches
text:
Three Millburn High School teams hosting county tourney matches October 14, 2015 Last updated: Wednesday, October 14, 2015, 3:46 PM By Jim Connelly 
Three Milburn High School varsity squads - girls volleyball, girls soccer and boys soccer - will open Essex County Tournament play at home. 
Seeding meetings for the three tournaments were held Oct. 13. 
The 15th-seeded Miller girls volleyball team is scheduled to meet 18th-seeded North 13th Street Tech in a preliminary round match Friday, Oct. 16, at Millburn High School at 4 p.m. 
Millburn and North 13th Street Tech will be meeting for the second time this season. The Millers prevailed 25-15, 19-25, 25-12 Oct. 1 in a Super Essex Conference, Colonial Division match at Millburn High School. 
The winner advances to face second-seeded Montclair Kimberley Academy in a first round match. First round play is scheduled to be completed by Saturday, Oct. 24. 
Millburn's boys and girls soccer teams open play in their respective county tournaments Wednesday, Oct. 21, at Dr. Keith A. Neigel Field. Match times had not been set as this issue of The Item of Millburn and Short Hills went to press. 
The girls soccer team, seeded seventh, will take on the winner of the preliminary round match between 10th-seeded Columbia High School and 15th-seeded Belleville High School. Preliminary round matches are scheduled to be played by Monday, Oct. 19. 
Second-seeded Glen Ridge High School will host the Millburn/Columbia/Belleville winner in the quarterfinals on Saturday, Oct. 24. 
The boys soccer team, seeded eighth, will take on ninth-seeded Nutley High School in first round action. 
The Millers and Raiders will be meeting for the second time this season. Millburn posted a 2-1 Super Essex Conference, American Division win over Nutley Oct. 2 at Neigel Field. 
Top-seeded West Orange High School, barring a first round upset loss to the winner of the preliminary round match between 16th-seeded Bloomfield Tech and 17th-seeded Belleville High School, will host the Millburn-Nutley winner in the Oct. 24 quarterfinals.
